{"id":"format-duplicate-unsupported","rule_id":"spec.unsupported-format-not-rejected","severity":"MEDIUM","file":"bin/cli.js","line":45,"message":"`const idx = argv.indexOf('--format');` inspects only the first occurrence. `node bin/cli.js version --format json --format yaml` exits 0 and prints `{\"version\":\"0.1.0\"}` instead of rejecting the non-`json` value with exit 1, violating the requirement that any unsupported `--format` value causes an error.","confidence":"high","verdict_binding":true}
